OL,3,CThe forgotten forest: Brazil's
OL,4,Cvanishing Cerrado
OL,6,FWhile global attention often centres
OL,7,Fon deforestation in the Amazon, vast
OL,8,Fareas of the Cerrado have been cleared
OL,9,Ffor cattle ranching and crop
OL,10,Fcultivation - especially soybeans.
OL,11,FEnvironmentalists are sounding the
OL,12,Falarm.
OL,14,FKnown as the "water tank of Brazil,"
OL,15,Fthe Cerrado feeds eight of the
OL,16,Fcountry's twelve largest river basins.
OL,17,FBut as land use changes, so does the
OL,18,Fclimate. Since the 1980s, rainfall has
OL,19,Fdropped by a third and temperatures
OL,20,Fhave risen by 1.5C.
