OL,3,CThe forgotten forest: Brazil's
OL,4,Cvanishing Cerrado
OL,6,FFires - once used as a controlled
OL,7,Fmethod to clear land - are
OL,8,Fincreasingly spreading uncontrollably.
OL,9,FAccording to Indigenous residents of
OL,10,FBacurizinho, 60% of their territory
OL,11,Fburned this year, destroying homes and
OL,12,Flivelihoods.
OL,14,FLocal teacher Cali blames large
OL,15,Fsoybean producers for the rising heat
OL,16,Fand worsening drought, which have
OL,17,Ffuelled more frequent and intense
OL,18,Ffires.
OL,20,F"When the water runs out," the
OL,21,Fvillagers say. "Everything is over."
