OL,3,CThe forgotten forest: Brazil's
OL,4,Cvanishing Cerrado
OL,6,FIt's a vicious cycle: the more land
OL,7,Fthat's cultivated, the more water is
OL,8,Fextracted for irrigation - and the
OL,9,Fwarmer the climate becomes.
OL,11,FThe Cerrado is often called the
OL,12,F"upside-down forest" because its
OL,13,Fvegetation grows extensive underground
OL,14,Froot networks that help it withstand
OL,15,Fdroughts and fires.
